	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Mthatha - An 11-year-old girl is one of two people who have
died in two separate road accidents over the weekend in Willowvale and
Butterworth, Eastern Cape police said on Sunday. The girl was hit by a car along the N2 road near Zingqayi
Village, Butterworth on Saturday morning, said Captain Jackson Manatha. She died on the scene. Police are still in the process of
officially notifying all her family members of her death. The cause of the accident is not known. Meanwhile, in a separate incident, the 30-year-old driver of
a car that was travelling on the R408 road from Dutywa to Willlowvale on
Saturday morning, died after the vehicle overturned. The driver died in hospital, while three passengers remain
in a critical condition. Two cases of culpable homicide have been opened by provincial
police. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  